<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Pickup + mm. 1–2: Light I-V walking harmony matching stately melody; m2 IV-V7-I with full V7 (Bb in LH bass)
- mm. 3–4: IV-V-vi-ii cycle at m3 (all four diatonic quarters); m4 V sus4→V7 suspension for half cadence
- mm. 5–8: Repeat with inversional variety; m6 IV soars to F5 in RH (Bb4-F5); m8 I half/half lyrical breathing space
- mm. 9–10: Final ii-V7-I with full LH at m9; pedal F1 at final cadence

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- m1→m2: LH F3 (I top) → Bb3 (IV top) — stepwise ascent
- m2 beat 2: V7 LH includes Bb3 and E3, giving tritone C-F#... wait, in F: C-E-G-Bb, so tritone is E-Bb; kept in bass register for richness
- m6: IV RH reaches Bb4-F5 — highest point in arrangement, matching phrase climax
- m9: ii7 with LH Bb3 reinforces subdominant color before final V7-I

TEXTURE ARC:
- Pickup–m2: sparse to moderate (2-note RH, 3-note LH)
- mm. 3–4: full quarter-beat harmonic rhythm; V sus4 suspension
- mm. 5–7: similar to phrase 1, RH reaching F5 at m6 peak
- mm. 8–10: lyrical half-note I, then full final cadence with pedal F1
-->
